answers.answer: Hi!Unremarkable means the findings are not consistent with any diagnosis and may be an incidental finding. Such findings are seen in people with high blood pressure, diabetes, high cholesterol, and hyperlipidemia. Please discuss with your doctor. Take care!The medical advice given should not be considered a substitute for medical care provided by a doctor who can examine you.
